function Start(idActorSpawned, idActorSpawner)
	Hydra.Wait(5)
	idTalkingChest = idActorSpawned
	local tNearbySpawnLocs = Hydra.FindSpawnLocsNearPlayer(idSelf, "Dungeon_Clicky_Any", 10, 30, false, true)
	
	if #tNearbySpawnLocs < 3 then
		Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(Hydra.ActorSpawnActor(S_REALCHEST, idTalkingChest, false, 0, 0), false)
		Hydra.ActorDelete(idTalkingChest)
	else
		Hydra.ActorSetConversationList(idTalkingChest, S_CONV_MAGICWORDS_01)
		--Placing the runescripts at different available spots
		nRandLoc = Hydra.GetRandomInt(1, #tNearbySpawnLocs)
		idRuneScript01 = Hydra.ActorSpawnActor(S_RUNESCRIPT_01, tNearbySpawnLocs[nRandLoc], tNearbySpawnLocs[nRandLoc], false, 0, 0)
		table.remove(tNearbySpawnLocs, nRandLoc)
		
		nRandLoc = Hydra.GetRandomInt(1, #tNearbySpawnLocs)
		idRuneScript02 = Hydra.ActorSpawnActor(S_RUNESCRIPT_02, tNearbySpawnLocs[nRandLoc], tNearbySpawnLocs[nRandLoc], false, 0, 0)
		table.remove(tNearbySpawnLocs, nRandLoc)
		
		nRandLoc = Hydra.GetRandomInt(1, #tNearbySpawnLocs)
		idRuneScript03 = Hydra.ActorSpawnActor(S_RUNESCRIPT_03, tNearbySpawnLocs[nRandLoc], tNearbySpawnLocs[nRandLoc], false, 0, 0)
		table.remove(tNearbySpawnLocs, nRandLoc)
	end
	--NOTE: For whatever reason, removing this Wait creates a chance for the event to fail
	--It will spawn Jah Eth Lum as the words but the words will not work on the chest
	--Hydra.Wait(1)
	--Hydra.TraceScreen(tNearbySpawnLocs[1])
end

function Start(idActorNPC, sConversation, idActorPlayer)
	local idRealChest = Hydra.ACDID_INVALID
	if sConversation == idPhrase then
		idRealChest = Hydra.ActorSpawnActor(S_REALCHEST, idTalkingChest, false, 0, 0)
		Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idRealChest, false)
		Hydra.ActorTriggerPowerAtFeet(idRealChest, S_PWR_KNOCKBACK)
	else
		Hydra.ActorTriggerPowerAtFeet(idSelf, S_PWR_KNOCKBACK)
	end
	
	Hydra.ActorPlayEffectGroup(idSelf, S_FX_CHESTBLAST)
	Hydra.ActorDelete(idTalkingChest)
	
	Hydra.ActorFadeAndDelete(idRuneScript01, 3)
	Hydra.ActorFadeAndDelete(idRuneScript02, 3)
	Hydra.ActorFadeAndDelete(idRuneScript03, 3)
end

unk_993f312.value:
nWordsSaid = 0

--List of complete phrases
tPhrases = 		{
				S_PHRASE_01,
				S_PHRASE_02,
				S_PHRASE_03,
				S_PHRASE_04,
				S_PHRASE_05,
				S_PHRASE_06,
				S_PHRASE_07,
				S_PHRASE_08
				}

--The 3 lists of magic words for variation
tWordSet01 = 	{
				S_MAGICWORD_Vemp,
				S_MAGICWORD_Sint
				}
				
tWordSet02 = 	{
				S_MAGICWORD_Et,
				S_MAGICWORD_La
				}
				
tWordSet03 = 	{
				S_MAGICWORD_Maldus,
				S_MAGICWORD_Palox
				}

--The actual pages with the words the players find
idRuneScript01 = Hydra.ACDID_INVALID
idRuneScript02 = Hydra.ACDID_INVALID
idRuneScript03 = Hydra.ACDID_INVALID

--Chests
idTalkingChest = Hydra.ActorsLinkedByActorInGroup(idSelf, "TALKINGCHEST")[1]
Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idTalkingChest, false)

--Words on the pages
idWord01 = Hydra.ACDID_INVALID
idWord02 = Hydra.ACDID_INVALID
idWord03 = Hydra.ACDID_INVALID


--Selecting a magic phrase and assigning the right words to the scattered pages
nRandWord = Hydra.GetRandomInt(0, 7)
idPhrase = tPhrases[nRandWord+1]

--Da heck is this?
--Since the magic words are paired up (2 to each word slot)
--it was simple enough to make a binary logic check to determine which words
--to scatter without having to check for each phrase individually
idWord01 = tWordSet01[1]
idWord02 = tWordSet02[1]
idWord03 = tWordSet03[1]

if nRandWord > 4 then
	idWord01 = tWordSet01[2]
end
if (nRandWord % 4 > 1) then
	idWord02 = tWordSet02[2]
end
if nRandWord % 2 > 0 then
	idWord03 = tWordSet03[2]
end
